body_text:
I think a slightly cleaner way to put that would be
try {
  return await response.json();
} catch(e) {
  return null;
}
This has the return await that we've been talking about in linting lately, but in this case it is actually needed (for the reason @andymikulski pointed out), and the linter understands this and will let it go.

body:
I think a slightly cleaner way to put that would be 

```js
try {
  return await response.json();
} catch(e) {
  return null;
}
```

This has the `return await` that we've been talking about in linting lately, but in this case it is actually needed (for the reason @andymikulski pointed out), and the linter understands this and will let it go.
